{code}
scala> val q"..$_; $_($_: ${tpe: Type})" = 
     |   typecheck(q"""
     |     def id(i: Int) = i
     |     val a = 42
     |     id(a)
     |   """)
tpe: reflect.runtime.universe.Type = Int
{code}
i.e. piggyback on ascription syntax to extract tree.tpe in pattern matching.
Alternatively the same can be done through magic annotation as in SI-8250 but ascription looks more elegant for this purpose. 
